        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 28 at 11:03PM EDT by NWS Upton NY</headline>
        <description>At 1102 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a developing thunderstorm
over Dix Hills, or over Brentwood, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Hauppauge and Smithtown around 1110 PM EDT.
Centereach and Stony Brook around 1120 PM EDT.
Port Jefferson around 1125 PM EDT.
Mount Sinai around 1130 PM EDT.
</description>
        <instruction>Heavy rain is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized ponding.</instruction>
